Description of problem: trying to open a google drive text file from within nautilus, possibly having a size of 0 bytes.
Version-Release number of selected component: gvfs-goa-1.28.2-1.fc24
Additional info: reporter: libreport-2.7.2 backtrace_rating: 4 cmdline: /usr/libexec/gvfsd-google --spawner :1.13 /org/gtk/gvfs/exec_spaw/39 crash_function: gdata_download_stream_read executable: /usr/libexec/gvfsd-google global_pid: 29998 kernel: 4.6.4-301.fc24.x86_64 pkg_fingerprint: 73BD E983 81B4 6521 pkg_vendor: Fedora Project runlevel: N 5 type: CCpp uid: 1000

(In reply to lennart_reuther from comment #0) > Description of problem: > trying to open a google drive text file from within nautilus, possibly > having a size of 0 bytes.
Thanks for your bug report. That's a good catch, I am able to reproduce it with an empty file, I will debug it further...
:-) ...always happy to help.
Actually, this is a bug in libgdata. I've proposed upstream fix for it, see: https://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=769727
